Beef Braising Ribs
results.description:
Cut from Canada AA or higher.

Beef short ribs (or back ribs) are rectangles of beef containing layers of fat, meat, and rib bone. They are usually taken from the chuck and short plate cuts of the cow. Short ribs are best enjoyed braised and slow cooked with liquid to produce tender meat and flavourful au jus.

results.name: Flank Steak, London Broil

Cut from Canada AA or higher.

Flank steak is a thin, boneless cut of beef that is typically marinated, cooked whole, and sliced. Add flank steak to your stir-fry or fajitas, or grill and serve with a side of sautéed mushrooms.
